Hyper Fixation and food are a big deal when you have ADHD. 

It’s hard to choose what I want, from where and even the “when” I’ll actually eat.

Sometimes I forget to eat all together. Drinking water falls into this category too. 

When I have a “favorite” meal I’ll make it over & over & over… until I’m sick of it… after that? I have no idea what to shop for or cook. Do I want to order out?… 

These questions cause so much anxiety and stress sometimes I’ll cry 😢 

Routine meal times & meal prep nutrition plans are helpful… But sometimes? I just get STUCK!

Mental Health Day

We all need & deserve mental health days. To take a break from the overwhelming. And we deserve to do so without guilt or shame. 

I struggle with this constantly. I’ve been working on my mental health through therapy, medications, shadow work and mindfulness… I started 2 years ago, when it finally came to the point of no return. I was now fighting for my life. 

I wish I could say this is a new journey for me… sadly it’s been a battle for as long as I can remember. 

•Uncountable dips into depressions 
•manic episodes 
•PTSD
•constant feelings of failing/being a burden
•multiple attempts to end my life. 

The last one was a miracle in itself, being brought back from the dead and given yet ANOTHER chance to try.

Some days are so easy, I just wake up and pop to it like it’s nothing… Then there’s days like today. I woke up feeling… off. Then proceeded to get more & more upset because I couldn’t place where the upset was coming from. 

Fast forward three hours later of me crying… stuck on my bed with a trauma loop playing on repeat in my head… I’m lucky to have disassociated enough to make this post.

I’m sharing this, showing the three emotional support squishes (blanket, stuffie, kitty stress squish) I need to feel safe/secure. I’ll most likely spend the day on the couch, watching comfort shows/movies. And hyper Fixation snacks if I’m lucky. I currently have none so eating has been a struggle lately.

I know that this day will pass. I know that my feelings, whatever they stem from, are valid. I know that this day is needed and will ultimately benefit my mental health. 

The same goes for you! You matter, your self care is important. Do what is necessary to get through your hard days. Reach out to your support system. Don’t give up the fight!

Sinead O’Connor

Today is a sad day. We say goodbye to the talented #sineadoconnor she was 56, and it was too soon. 

Hearing that it’s connected to her mental health is just so heartbreaking. Not knowing her personally doesn’t take away from being able to relate to her struggles. 

I know so many of us are struggling daily with depression and other mental health issues too. We’re all human, our emotions are valid. And we never know what someone is dealing with or going through. 

Please be kind to yourself and one another. Kindness is free… and we could all benefit from more kindness in the world. 

To Sinead O’Conner I hope you are at peace. To her surviving friends & family my heart goes out to you.

Pain Level 0

I’ve been fortunate enough to have an extremely active life. MBX state champion at 6. Track & Field, cross country, basketball, volleyball, weightlifting, beginning wrestler both semi comp & I know high flying pro moves with many thanks to @darth_irene 

*there is also chronic pain/fatigue that comes with my mental health issues. Depression, anxiety and so much more HURTS! Constantly in a state of fight, Flight or freeze… not able to relax always feeling tense? I cry in frustration at how much I have to tell myself daily “drop your shoulders girl, don’t lock your knees… you’re safe 😭” 

(I’ve never really gone in depth with this stuff so thanks for reading)

I’m blessed to have a life of celebrating the strength and movement that my body has done, and can still do! With the sweet comes the sour. Paying the price through injury and simply age caused wear & tear… I’ll take it. 

The things that hurt most are my spinal cord injury, my shoulders dislocating constantly and now recently my jaw too… I’m sure there’s so many of you that have lists like this. Days where you sit on your bed crying because your body hurts so bad and you feel ALONE. No one can feel it but you, you can look totally normal to the world. You might hear insults like “You’re too young to be in pain/injured like that” or “You’re pain isn’t valid because you didn’t get hurt the way I DID” or my PERSONAL FAVORITE “just go get an adjustment” chiropractor’s medical malpractice insurance says they can’t even touch me because of my spinal cord injury.

My days are consumed with activities to improve my quality of life. Pain management, chronic health issues, mental health management… it’s exhausting just LIVING. to be in this moment of zero pain. Breathing and it’s a full breath. To simply be. I’m so incredibly grateful. Thank you body for carrying me, even with all you go through. I just want you fellow warriors & supporters to know how amazing you are. That you are an inspiration to others and to share your stories. #pain #chronicillness #chronicpainwarrior #dislocatedshoulder #painless #relief #fyp #viral #mentalhealth #tense #relax #surreal

Let’s Talk Meds Baby

To all my chronic illnesses/pain/mental health warriors… We ALL know that medication management is PIVOTAL for our wellness plans. When those levels are off… everything is off. 

One of the things I struggle with is keeping up with my appointments, especially when an actual office building is required. Ask me to come in for tests it’s even worse. I fear hearing that one more thing could go wrong, that a new specialist is needed… 

But not making those appointments, letting prescriptions lapse or missing blood work means that my entire internal system gets rocked like it’s at a heavy metal concert. 

So a lot of my life is centered on self care, mental health matters and appointment upon appointment and … that’s right YOU GUESSED IT… more appointments!!! 

Just living can be exhausting! So if you’re going through it like me? I see you! I’m proud of you! Keep going darling, your health matters!! 

If you’re a chronic warriors companion in any way? I see you too!! There’s nothing worse than watching the ones you love struggle, knowing there’s nothing you can do. If this is a new journey for you, be kind to yourself and others. Have patience, and keep the faith! With time you’ll find what works best for you!

You look over and see this slinking flirty little thing. She keeps looking up at you with those big eyes and cutely swishing her tail in a “come hither and pet me human” kinda way…

But they wouldn’t know, would they?… Then it happens. They nudge your hand… you can no longer resist. Before you know it, they are in your lap purring and you are giving them the scratches under the chin and around the ears…

Let both cool. Peel eggs. Chop bacon. Halve the eggs and spoon the yolks into a bowl. 

Break up the yolks with a fork or blender. Add the Kraft EVOO Mayo until you reach the desired consistency. Whip with the fork/mixer again. 

Sprinkle in paprika, crushed chili pepper seeds, Himalayan, pink salt, and pepper. Whip again until well blended.

Scoop mixture into a piping bag. *If you don’t have one a ziplock bag will suffice, just fill, then cut one corner off. 😉

Pipe into empty halved cooked eggs. Lightly sprinkle with more paprika. Garnish with chopped bacon. 

Feel free to spruce up this recipe in any way you’d like!

BIPOLAR REALITY ☑️

For starters, yes I am bipolar 1 (manic & depressive episodes). I am medicated, with psychiatric & therapist support. I do have other disorders such as ADHD That also means my emotions are very hard to regulate. 

This morning I woke up feeling good. 🌞 I was excited to get up and out on a walk at 6 am before the sun got too high. Came home, ate my oats with peanut 🥜 butter, set up my at home workout… boom… out of nowhere comes a complete overwhelming cloud of darkness. Pain all the way in my heart. I had trouble breathing. Sobbing from the bottom of my soul. 

This happens more mornings than I care to count per month. Perhaps it’s because I’m up EARLY and alone? It happens 1/2 hr to an hour after my morning walks usually… please see @theworkoutwitch_ on how trauma releases from you hips from somatic exercise and walking helps in this aspect also. 

All I do know is these episodes SUCK. They derail my day, devastate mentally and bring me to my knees begging for it to stop. I can’t even tell you what “IT” Is. 

I am not “crazy” 🤪 I just feel so very deeply. Being an Empath on top of it all takes the cake. Just know this with the lows being what they are, the highs are great as long as they’re under supervision. 

This post is only meant to enlighten. To inspire others to seek help & treatment if my story helps theirs make sense. To show you into my life so you know bipolar people… shocker… are people!! We’re intelligent, funny, talented, strong and fragile at the same time. At the center? People just like the rest of the world. Deserving of acknowledgement and love. 

If you’re a bipolar buddy? I see you 👀 boo!! 👏👏 keep going!! A bipolar loved one? You are appreciated!! Keep loving with open hearts, We need more people like you. 🥰

911 if it’s a medical emergency.

Words to Live By 

🛑You don’t owe anyone an explanation. An apology or excuse. 🙅🏼‍♀️

We are constantly thrust upon these expectations of communication or assimilation. To placate others (Ⓜ️en/S🅾️ciety) and lessen ourselves to better “fit in”.

ALL THE NO! 

You deserve the same space and respect to speak & be heard as everyone else. DON’T be afraid to remind anyone of this.

No one can “tell you” how it’s going to be, it’s a deniable request. 

NEVER under ANY circumstance apologize for being or sharing space. You are valuable and deserve to be there the same as anyone. You deserve your time & turn. 

Use terms like “excuse or pardon me”. You’re still offering respect, while maintaining your own personal respect. ✊ 

Lastly, speak up for yourself. Remind them you’re not there to be walked over.

“Excuse me, I wasn’t finished speaking yet.” Use this term strongly. Pause for 3 sec and maintain your gaze/tone. Then resume with your sentence/point. 

Embrace your power darlings. They will rise up to meet you. 🙏🏻 @winningalphawomen @bossedup.mindset
